#Back and Forground: 
----------------------
>>> command & | Run the command in BackGround 

>>> jobs | List jobs running in BackGround 

>>> fg %[n] | Froground job number %[n]


----------------------------------------------------------------------------
#make the running command in background : 

>>> ping google.com 

>>> clt+z   | jobs make it suspended and background 

>>> bg 

>>> jobs | for chcek the jobs 

>>> fg %[number_of_jobs]
----------------------------------------------------------------------------
----------------------------------------------------------------------------

--------------------------Process Management : Tmux--------------------------------------------------
----------------------------------------------------------------------------
#start the tmux : 
>>> tmux

#run any command with terminal after that run on background : 
>>> tmux | back & forground like previous jobs. 
    >>>clt+b , then D | detuch tmux. 


>>> tmux list-sessions - List sessions. 

>>> tmux attach | attach session 

>>> nohup command & | run command in background even session in background .
